WEBVTT

00:00.923 --> 00:02.860
Previously on
<i>The Big Bang Theory...</i>

00:02.924 --> 00:05.307
We were worried
about you.

00:05.309 --> 00:07.309
Don't be melodramatic.

00:07.311 --> 00:08.928
I'm just getting on a train

00:08.930 --> 00:11.096
and leaving forever.

00:11.098 --> 00:14.350
So a few things
don't go your way

00:14.352 --> 00:15.684
and your best
decision

00:15.686 --> 00:18.320
is to ride the
rails like a hobo?

00:18.322 --> 00:20.606
Leonard, I am overwhelmed.

00:20.608 --> 00:21.690
Everything
is changing,

00:21.692 --> 00:24.109
and it's simply too much.

00:24.111 --> 00:25.778
I need to get away and think.

00:25.780 --> 00:27.279
Sheldon...

00:27.281 --> 00:29.114
Yes?

00:29.116 --> 00:31.000
I'm gonna miss you.

00:31.002 --> 00:33.836
Of course you are.

00:35.372 --> 00:37.957
You just made
that easier.

00:41.928 --> 00:44.096
Excuse me.

00:46.917 --> 00:48.884
Is it at all possible

00:48.886 --> 00:51.136
that you're knitting
a pair of pants?

00:52.772 --> 00:55.057
Oh, well, no, you're
understandably terrified.

00:55.059 --> 00:57.693
But, you know,
allow me to explain.

00:57.695 --> 01:00.813
45 days ago, um,
I embarked on

01:00.815 --> 01:02.314
a railroad journey
of healing

01:02.316 --> 01:03.699
because my university

01:03.701 --> 01:05.316
was making me do
string theory,

01:05.319 --> 01:07.903
and my favorite comic
book store burned down,

01:07.905 --> 01:09.738
and when my roommate
got engaged,

01:09.740 --> 01:11.991
my girlfriend wanted
to move in with me,

01:11.993 --> 01:14.660
which was no doubt
a ploy just to see my--

01:14.662 --> 01:17.246
well, excuse my language,
but my bathing suit parts.

01:20.917 --> 01:22.885
Uh, sir, may I
use your phone?

01:22.887 --> 01:24.920
I don't think so.
Yeah, well,

01:24.922 --> 01:26.672
I understand that
I'm half naked,

01:26.674 --> 01:28.557
but there is
a reasonable explanation.

01:28.559 --> 01:31.176
While I slept
in my sleeper car,

01:31.178 --> 01:32.978
all my possessions were stolen.

01:32.980 --> 01:33.980
Now,

01:33.981 --> 01:35.648
typically,
I wear pajamas,

01:35.650 --> 01:39.518
but I recently adopted
a hobo lifestyle

01:39.520 --> 01:43.272
and pajamas are the
sleep-pants of the Man.

01:45.191 --> 01:48.243
I'll have you know,
Mahatma Gandhi wore no pants

01:48.245 --> 01:50.162
and a nation rallied behind him!

01:50.164 --> 01:52.147
My good man...

01:52.149 --> 01:53.499
Now, before you walk away...

01:53.501 --> 01:55.367
I know that I may
appear deranged,

01:55.369 --> 01:57.870
but I am, in fact,
a world-renowned physicist.

01:57.872 --> 02:01.290
Ask me the difference
between a boson and a fermion.

02:01.292 --> 02:02.508
Go ahead, ask!

02:05.128 --> 02:07.046
Bosons have integer spin,

02:07.048 --> 02:09.431
fermions have half-integer spin!

02:09.433 --> 02:10.716
My legs are getting cold!

02:10.717 --> 02:13.485
Why won't anybody help me?

02:13.487 --> 02:17.106
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

02:17.108 --> 02:20.442
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

02:20.444 --> 02:22.061
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

02:22.063 --> 02:24.613
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

02:24.615 --> 02:27.282
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪<i> We built the pyramids</i> ♪

02:27.284 --> 02:29.952
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:29.954 --> 02:31.870
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

02:31.872 --> 02:32.719
♪<i> Bang!</i> ♪

02:32.720 --> 02:36.720
